==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Throwing stick
<hw>Throw"ing stick`</hw>. <fld>(Anthropol.)</fld> <def>An instrument
used by various savage races for throwing a spear; -- called also
<altname>throw stick</altname> and <altname>spear thrower</altname>. One
end of the stick receives the butt of the spear, as upon a hook or
thong, and the other end is grasped with the hand, which also holds the
spear, toward the middle, above it with the finger and thumb, the effect
being to bring the place of support nearer the center of the spear, and
practically lengthen the arm in the act of throwing. In Mexico, one such
device is called the <stype>atlatl</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thrown</ent>⟦br⟧
